---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { brand } from '../config/brand';
---
<Layout
  title="Make a Payment | Belvedere Decks"
  description="Pay your Belvedere Decks invoice. Payments follow the three-installment schedule in your contract: deposit, start of work, and final walkthrough."
>
  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container">
      <p class="eyebrow">Payments</p>
      <h1>Make a payment.</h1>
      <div class="rule"></div>
      <p class="lead">
        Every project follows the same simple schedule, written into your contract
        before work begins. No surprises here either.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="margin-top: 0;">How payments are structured</h2>
      <table class="stack">
        <tbody>
          <tr><th>1. At contract signing</th><td>One-third deposit. This reserves your build slot and covers material ordering.</td></tr>
          <tr><th>2. At start of work</th><td>One-third when materials are delivered and work begins.</td></tr>
          <tr><th>3. At completion</th><td>The final third after substantial completion and your final walkthrough, when you're satisfied.</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>

      <h2>Ways to pay</h2>
      <ul class="checklist">
        <li>Check, payable to {brand.legalName}</li>
        <li>Zelle <!-- TODO: add Zelle contact once business banking is live --></li>
        <li>Card payment online <!-- TODO: add processor link (next step - to be set up together) --></li>
      </ul>

      <!-- ONLINE PAYMENT BUTTON: uncomment and point at the processor link when ready.
      <p><a class="btn primary" href="TODO-PAYMENT-URL">Pay Your Invoice Online</a></p>
      -->

      <div class="notice">
        <strong>A note on Maryland law:</strong> home improvement deposits in Maryland are
        capped at one-third of the contract price, and we never ask for final payment
        until the work is substantially complete. If any contractor asks for more up
        front, that's a red flag, ours included.
      </div>

      <p>
        Questions about an invoice? Call or text
        <a href={`tel:${brand.phone || brand.phoneDisplay}`}>{brand.phoneDisplay}</a>
        or email <a href={`mailto:${brand.email}`}>{brand.email}</a>.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
